spend the majority of their life under the controlling mental
influence of the other Wraith. It's not surprising if you remove
that influence, they revert to an animal state. But that shouldn't
happen with Todd, theoretically.
KELLER
Yeah, but you're forgetting one thing. I haven't found a cure for
the disease that was killing them. I mean, we take him out, and...he
might not last long.
SHEPPARD
Well, that's the one thing I like about the plan.
[An alarm beeps.]
MCKAY
Great.
[McKay checks a terminal.]
MCKAY
Okay, so navigation's acting up. Look, whatever we decide, we gotta
do it quickly because I cannot stay ahead of these malfunctions for
much longer.
[Sheppard bites his lip.]
INT--HIVE HIBERNATION POD AREA
[Ronon, Sheppard, and Teyla stand outside Todd's pod.]
RONON
You sure about this?
[Sheppard readies his rifle. Teyla deactivates the chamber. Todd
awakens and takes in the situation.]
TODD
Sheppard...
SHEPPARD
How are you feeling?
TODD
I did not think you would come.
RONON
(deadpan)
What are friends for?
TEYLA
Your ship is malfunctioning. We need you to fix it.
TODD
(caustically)
You woke me for this?
SHEPPARD
That's right. We've got work to do.
INT--HIVE BRIDGE
[Todd works some controls. McKay approaches. The rest of the team is
nearby.]
MCKAY
(hesitantly)
You know, I did...I tried that already.
[Todd snarls at McKay, who steps back, hand raised.]
MCKAY
(sighing)
Okay, all right. You know what? Just go ahead. Boy, somebody woke up
on the wrong side of the pod this morning.
TODD
This makes no sense. These systems are behaving erratically.
MCKAY
(annoyed)
Well, that's what I've been trying to tell you!
TODD
What have you done to them?!
MCKAY
I haven't done anything! They've been acting all screwy since the
