TODD
At the current level of the ship's degradation, I estimate we have
four days before it becomes uninhabitable.
SHEPPARD
Well, you better get to work.
[Todd growls and sniffs, then turns away.]
INT--HIVE BRIDGE
[Sheppard's team and Lorne rejoin McKay. Some marines stand guard
outside.]
SHEPPARD
How's it going, Rodney?
MCKAY
(annoyed)
Well, aside from the fact that every time I try to fix something,
something else breaks? Fine.
SHEPPARD
So we can expect more of these power fluctuations?
MCKAY
I think it's more than likely. It's probably going to get worse.
SHEPPARD
Then we've got a problem.
RONON
The other Wraith.
SHEPPARD
We can't afford to let them get out anymore.
MCKAY
Well, I have been able to identify that safety protocol I was
talking about. I won't be able to override it completely, but I
should be able to make a few key alterations.
SHEPPARD
Yeah? Like what?
MCKAY
Well, I mean the simplest thing to do would be to make it so the
pods don't release the Wraith when they shut down. That would kill
them. Basically, suffocate them.
RONON
Great! They're Wraith!
MCKAY
Yeah, but are they? I mean, they've taken the treatment. They no
longer feed.
LORNE
Tell that to Lieutenant Williams.
TEYLA
What about Todd? If significant numbers of his crew are killed, he
will demand to know why.
SHEPPARD
Just another malfunction. Do it.
MCKAY
All right.
[McKay enters some commands.]
INT--HIVE SCIENCE LAB
[Todd groans and huddles over a console.]
KELLER
You all right?
TODD
It will pass.
KELLER
I'm sorry. I never meant for any of this to happen. I honestly
thought the treatment would make things better for everyone.
[Todd laughs heartily.]
KELLER
What's funny?
TODD
I find it amusing. Human apologizing to Wraith.
KELLER
(caustic)
That's because you don't understand compassion. You just view it as
a sign of weakness.
TODD
Isn't it?
KELLER
No. Not by a long shot.
TODD
Ah. I'm not sure Colonel Sheppard would agree with you.
KELLER
Colonel Sheppard's a soldier. I'm a doctor.
TODD
(patronizing)
Ah, yes. His job is to take lives, and yours is to save them.
KELLER
No, his job is also to save lives. He just has a different...set of
tools.
TODD
Hmm.
INT--HIVE BRIDGE
MCKAY
All right...I've created a program to override the safety protocol.
You sure you want me to do this?
SHEPPARD
Go ahead.
MCKAY
All right.
[He types some commands. The monitor shows power shutting down in all
but one small area.]
TEYLA
What is that?
MCKAY
It's one of the hibernation chambers. It's not accepting the new
command.
[He tries again.]
MCKAY
No, it's no good. I can't access it from here.
SHEPPARD
How many of them are in them?
MCKAY
Well, it's one of the smaller auxiliary chambers, so...a-a couple of
dozen at the most?
SHEPPARD
All right. We're going to have to figure out another way to deal
with these guys.
[He reaches into a pack and pulls out some C-4.]
INT--HIVE CORRIDOR
[Sheppard, Lorne, Ronon, and Teyla head down the corridor. Teyla
pauses, sensing something.]
TEYLA
Colonel...
[A Wraith warrior appears behind them. They fire on the Wraith, killing
it.]
SHEPPARD
Well, that's not a good sign. Let's move.
INT--HIVE HIBERNATION POD AREA
[The lights flicker as they arrive.]
LORNE
Power fluctuations.
RONON
More of them might be out.
SHEPPARD
Oh, this is what I was afraid of.
(keying radio)
McKay?
INT--HIVE BRIDGE
SHEPPARD
(over radio)
We just figured out why you weren't able to access the last chamber.
MCKAY
(into radio)
What? What is it?
INT--POD CHAMBER
SHEPPARD
We're too late. The pods are opened.
INT--HIVE BRIDGE
MCKAY
How many got out?
INT--POD CHAMBER
[Sheppard looks at the levels of empty chambers, about 22 in all.]
SHEPPARD
All of them.
INT--HIVE CORRIDOR
[Sheppard briefs his team, sans McKay, Lorne's team, and the other
marines.</blockquote>
SHEPPARD
All right, we're going to split into teams. We're going to divide
each deck into four sections. We're going to sweep through starting
from this position. Don't take any chances. Shoot anything that
moves. Everyone clear?
[They nod.]
SHEPPARD
All right, let's move out.
[Ronon and a marine move along one area.]
[Teyla spots a Wraith and shoots it. She and Ramirez continue on.]
[Sheppard and his marine run into two more Wraith and kill them.]
INT--HIVE SCIENCE LAB
TODD
(intrigued)
It says here you attempted to use the Iratus DNA in your treatment.
KELLER
Yeah, I thought using the pure DNA of an Iratus bug would help
prevent the deterioration of your Wraith abilities. Got the idea
from Michael if you can believe that, but unfortunately it didn't
work, so...
[She notices Todd's distracted expression.]
KELLER
What is it?
TODD
I have an idea.
INT--HIVE CORRIDOR
[Sheppard patrols with his marine, checking all the Wraith are dead.]
KELLER
(over radio)
Colonel Sheppard, come in please?
SHEPPARD
(into radio)
This is Sheppard.
INT--HIVE SCIENCE LAB
KELLER
(over radio)
You need to come down to the lab right away. Todd needs to speak to
you.
SHEPPARD
(irritated, over radio)
I'm a little busy right now. Can it wait?
KELLER
Apparently not.
INT--HIVE CORRIDOR
SHEPPARD
(to marine)
Meet up with Teyla and Ramirez until I get back.
INT--CORRIDOR OUTSIDE HIVE SCIENCE LAB
[Keller meets Sheppard outside the science lab.]
SHEPPARD
What's so damn important?
KELLER
He says there's a way to fix this.
INT--HIVE SCIENCE LAB
SHEPPARD
Fix what? Cure the disease?
TODD
Not cure it. But undo it.
SHEPPARD
(impatient)
What are you talking about?
TODD
As you know, healthy Wraith have an inherent ability to heal
